A DRIVER was killed when his vehicle collided with an articulated lorry.&nbsp;The 49-year-old was behind the wheel of a cattle float on the M74 near to Elvanfoot, Lanarkshire.The crash between the two Scania-make vehicles happened at around 1.20pm on Wednesday.The driver of the cattle float was pronounced dead at the scene while the 45-year-old driver of the other vehicle was not injured.Constable Kenneth Beeby, from Road Policing in Motherwell, said: &quot;I would appeal to anyone who has information to contact police via the non-emergency number 101.&quot;